:"The `n`th eigenfunction of the Harmonic oscillator is defined as the function `ℝ → ℂ`\ntaking `x : ℝ` to\n\n`1/√(2^n n!) 1/√(√π ξ) * physHermite n (x / ξ) * e ^ (- x²/ (2 ξ²))`.\n\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QuantumMechanics/OneDimension/HarmonicOscillator/Eigenfunction.html#QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.eigenfunction","kind":"def","line":23,"name":"QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.eigenfunction","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L23-L31"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.Basic","PhysLean.Mathematics.SpecialFunctions.PhysHermite"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.QuantumMechanics.OneDimension.HarmonicOscillator.Eigenfunction"}